description._content:
Programme for a concert held at Naylor's Theatre in Deseronto, Ontario, on March 14th, 1929.

"Programme
Naylor's Theatre, Deseronto, Thursday, March 14, 1929.

PART I.
1. Piano Duett.....'Jampa'.....Herold 
Miss Stewart and Mr. Eppes.

2. Piano.....(a) 'The Snow Man'.....Presser
A. Argue
(b) 'In Joyland'.....Presser
H. Therrien
(c) 'Grand Father's Clock'.....Pira
R. Boyce

3. Vocal.....'Friends of Yesterday'.....German
Mr. Tunnicliffe

4. Piano.....(a) 'At the Farm'.....Fenton
F. Dawson
(b) 'The Mill Wheel'.....Kroeger
J. Rendell
(c) 'Rondo'.....Dussek
L. Rowsom

5.. Vocal.....'My Gentle Child'.....Reigo
Miss Metcalfe

6. Reading.....'A Voice from a Far Country'.....
Miss McCullough

7. Vocal.....'Ever So Far Away'.....Adams
Mr. Pearce

8. Piano.....(a) 'Polish Dance'......Mero
F. McKinney
(b) 'In the Swing'.....Brenner
E. Johnston
(c) 'Valse'.....Greig
L. Bowen

9. Vocal.....'My To-Morrow'.....Stott
Mr. Tunnicliffe

10. Piano.....'The Wanderer's Return'.....Lange
B. St. Louis

11. Saxaphone [saxophone].....'Welsh Air'.....
Mr. Maxwell

12. Piano.....'Dance Rustique'.....Smith
H. Seales

13. Quartette.....'A Catastrophe'.....

PART II

1. Piano.....'La Coquette Valse'.....Backmann
Miss R. Smith

2. Vocal.....'Glorious Devon'.....German
Mr. Tunnicliffe

3. Piano.....(a) 'Valetta'.....Krogman
(b) 'Country Dance'.....Sartorio
M. Field

4. Vocal.....'Garden of Roses'.....Wood
Mrs. Boyce

5. Piano.....'Berceuse'.....Godard
'Prelude in C. Sharp Minor'.....Rackmaninoff

6. Vocal.....'Alanna'.....Lohr
Mr. Pearce

7. Piano.....(a) 'Prelude'.....Chopin
(b) 'Etude Caprice' .....Loetz
K. McCullough

8. Vocal.....'Wind Song'.....Rogers
'The Birth of Morn'.....Leoni
Miss Metcalfe

9. Piano.....(a) 'Solfiegietto'.....Bach
(b) 'Valse Caprice'.....Tellier
Miss Blake

10. Reading.....
Miss McCullough

11. Piano.....'Scarf Dance'.....Chaminade
Miss Bowen

12. Vocal.....'Until'.....Sanderson
Mr. Tunnicliffe

13. Quartette.....'Doan Ye Cry, Ma Honey'.....

GOD SAVE THE KING"

One of a number of items which originally belonged to Cecil and Elizabeth Argue of Deseronto, Ontario. Donated to the Archives in October 2013.
